ion or photon loss in a wide variety\nof coherent and incoherent linear systems including those, for example, in\natmospheric imaging, time-domain spectroscopy, ${\\cal PT}$ symmetric\nnon-Hermitian photonics, and even quantum computing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 May 2019 21:58:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Nov 2019 03:57:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 1 Jul 2020 21:36:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-26"}
